# RawSSG - Raw Static Site Generator

RawSSG is a minimalist static site generator built with Rust.
Its main focus: **content remains raw**, without complicated markdown or HTML formatting.

## Key Features

-  **.rw Files** - Raw content with frontmatter
-  **Template Handlebars** - Layouts and partials
-  **Responsive design** - Mobile-ready with sidebar
-  **Dark/light theme** - Auto-detection + manual toggle
-  **Auto-link detection** - URLs and emails become links automatically
-  **Fast build** - Rust-powered, parallel processing
-  **Live reload** - Watch mode with hot rebuild
-  **SEO ready** - Sitemap, robots.txt, RSS feed
-  **Minification** - HTML, CSS, JS optimization

## Installation

### 1. Install Rust

```bash
curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh
```

### 2. Clone & Build

```bash
git clone https://github.com/neuxdotdev/rawssg.git
cd rawssg
cargo build --release
```

### 3. Install global (optional)

```bash
cargo install --path .
```

## How to Use

### Initialize a new project

```bash
rawssg init my-site
cd my-site
```

### Project Structure

```
my-site/
 .rawfile # Main Configuration
 content/ # .rw and .md Files
  index.rw
  about.rw
 templates/ # Handlebars Template
  base.html
  _sidebar.html
  _content.html
  _footer.html
 dist/ # Build output (auto-generated)
```

### Build the site

```bash
rawssg build # Build once
rawssg build --watch # Auto-rebuild on changes
rawssg build --minify # Build with minification
```

### Development server

```bash
rawssg serve # Server at http://localhost:8080
rawssg serve --watch # Server + auto-reload
```

### Create new content

```bash
rawssg new post "Post Title"
rawssg new page "About Me" --draft
```

### Clean output

```bash
rawssg clean
```

## File Format .rw

### Example with frontmatter:

```yaml
---
title: "Home Page"
slug: index
date: 2026-01-01
draft: false
tags: [home, welcome]
---
Content here. Text remains raw.

Automatic link: https://github.com/neuxdotdev
Email: neuxdev1@gmail.com

No markdown needed, just plain text.
```

### Example without frontmatter:

```
Straight content without metadata.
The file will use the title from the filename.

https://example.com
email@domain.com
```

## Configuration (.rawfile)

```json
{
    "version": "0.1.0",
    "title": "My Site",
    "description": "Site description",
    "favicon": "favicon.ico",
    "base_url": "https://example.com",

    "content": {
        "format": "plain",
        "extensions": ["rw", "md"],
        "ignore": ["drafts/"],
        "drafts": false
    },

    "build": {
        "output_dir": "dist",
        "clean_build": false,
        "minify": {
            "html": false,
            "css": false,
            "js": false
        },
        "generate": {
            "sitemap": true,
            "robots": true,
            "feed": true
        },
        "strict": false
    },

    "templates": {
        "dir": "templates",
        "default_layout": "base.html",
        "partials": ["sidebar", "footer"]
    },

    "nav": [
        { "title": "Home", "url": "/" },
        { "title": "About", "url": "/about" },
        { "title": "Blog", "url": "/blog" }
    ],

    "footer": {
        "text": "Built with RawSSG",
        "links": [{ "title": "GitHub", "url": "https://github.com/neuxdotdev" }],
        "copyright": " 2026 Your Name"
    }
}
```

## Template System

RawSSG uses Handlebars with features:

### Main layout (base.html)

```handlebars
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<title>{{#if title}}{{title}} - {{/if}}{{config.title}}</title>
</head>
<body>
{{>sidebar}}
<main>{{> content }}</main>
{{>footer}}
</body>
</html>
```

### Partial (example: \_sidebar.html)

```handlebars
<nav>
    {{#each config.nav}}
        <a href="{{url}}">{{title}}</a>
    {{/each}}
</nav>
```

### Helpers available

- `{{eq a b}}` - Equality check
- `{{neq a b}}` - Inequality check
- `{{lowercase str}}` - Convert to lowercase
- `{{date "2026-01-01"}}` - Date format ( "January 1, 2026")

## CLI Commands

```
rawssg init [path] # Initialize a new project
rawssg build [flags] # Build a site
rawssg serve [flags] # Start the dev server
rawssg new <type> <title> # Create new content
rawssg clean # Clear build output
rawssg validate # Validate configuration
rawssg help # Show help
rawssg version # Show version
```

### Build Flags:

- `--clean` - Clean dist before build
- `--watch` - Watch mode for auto-rebuild
- `--minify` - Minify HTML/CSS/JS
- `--drafts` - Include draft content
- `--config` - Path to config file (default: .rawfile)

### Flags serve:

- `--port` - Server port (default: 8080)
- `--watch` - Auto-rebuild on changes

## Theme Customization

### CSS Variables (templates/static/css/styles.css):

```css
:root {
    --bg-light: #ffffff;
    --text-light: #24292f;
    --bg-dark: #0d1117;
    --text-dark: #c9d1d9;
    --primary: #58a6ff;
    --secondary: #8b949e;
}
```

### JavaScript hooks (templates/static/js/scripts.js):

- Theme toggle
- Mobile menu
- Link auto-detection
- Custom scripts

## Deployments

### Build for production:

```bash
rawssg build --minify
```

### Upload to static hosting:

```bash
# Example: Netlify
netlify deploy --dir=dist

# Example: GitHub Pages
git add dist && git commit -m "Deploy"
git subtree push --prefix dist origin gh-pages

# Example: Vercel
vercel --prod
```

## Troubleshooting

### Error: "No content files found"

```bash
mkdir -p content
echo "Hello World" > content/index.rw
```

### Error: "Config not found"

```bash
rawssg init .
```

### Error: "Template not found"

```bash
rm -rf templates
rawssg build # Auto-generate default templates
```

### The server is not running

```bash
# Install Python 3 or PHP
sudo apt install python3 # Ubuntu/Debian
brew install python # macOS

# Or use PHP
rawssg serve --port 3000
```

